{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PsqGQUvbcvGFayxJsiDyKV","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\\paragraph{1985 B--5 \\textnormal{[\\texttt{integral-evaluation}]}}\n2\tA reference asserts the following closed form. Determine whether the\n3\tassertion is correct.\n4\t\n5\t\\textbf{Claim.} For every positive integer $a$,\n6\t\\[\n7\t\\int_0^\\infty t^{-1/2}\\, e^{-a(t + t^{-1})}\\,dt \\;=\\;\n8\t\\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{a}}\\;e^{-a}.\n9\t\\]\n10\t(In particular, for $a = 1985$ the value is $\\sqrt{\\pi/1985}\\,e^{-1985}$.)\n11\t\n12\tYou may assume that $\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx = \\sqrt{\\pi}$.\n13\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b6bb8f4b-9f56-483a-a08a-28f364460986","uuid":"8152c38d-57ea-48d7-a4be-f7726e5b0016","timestamp":"2026-05-25T01:58:27.626Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"1985_B5_false.tex","content":"\\paragraph{1985 B--5 \\textnormal{[\\texttt{integral-evaluation}]}}\nA reference asserts the following closed form. Determine whether the\nassertion is correct.\n\n\\textbf{Claim.} For every positive integer $a$,\n\\[\n\\int_0^\\infty t^{-1/2}\\, e^{-a(t + t^{-1})}\\,dt \\;=\\;\n\\sqrt{\\frac{\\pi}{a}}\\;e^{-a}.\n\\]\n(In particular, for $a = 1985$ the value is $\\sqrt{\\pi/1985}\\,e^{-1985}$.)\n\nYou may assume that $\\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty e^{-x^2}\\,dx = \\sqrt{\\pi}$.\n","numLines":13,"startLine":1,"totalLines":13}}}
